item.title: [+771] U.S. Senate passed an $871 billion health care reform plan
item.description: Washington (CNN) -- The Senate has started the final day of deliberations on passage of a sweeping $871 billion health care bill. A vote is expected shortly after 7 a.m. ET.The Senate health care bill cleared a third and final procedural hurdle Wednesday as Democrats successfully limited remaining debate time on the $871 billion measure.

item.title: [+533] Tennessee Man Buys Gas For 80 Strangers
item.description: Drivers filling up at a Tennessee gas station got an unexpected holiday gift at the pump. A local resident, Don Reed, bought gas for 80 strangers, and then sent them on their way with a smile.

item.title: [+520] How Wikipedia’s green doctor rewrote 5,428 climate articles
item.description: The Climategate Emails describe how a small band of climatologists cooked the books to rewrite history as well as science, particularly by eliminating the Medieval Warm Period. The emails reveal something else, too: the enlistment of the most widely read source of information in the world — Wikipedia — in the wholesale rewriting of this history.

item.title: [+496] Sean Hannity's Bogus Russian Climate Scandal
item.description: Fox's Sean Hannity recently reported a "bombshell" revelation that "a major Russian climate change organization" had its data tampered with by leading British climate scientists. But this "climate change organization" is actually an economic think tank with ties to US oil companies and no climate data or climatologists of its own.
